# shadcn-svelte UI conventions

Use primitives from `$lib/components/ui` for interactive controls. Config: [components.json](../../components.json).

## Required mappings

| Raw HTML | Use instead |
|----------|-------------|
| `<button>` | `{ Button }` from `$lib/components/ui/button` |
| `<input>` (text, search, etc.) | `{ Input }` from `$lib/components/ui/input` |
| `<textarea>` | `{ Textarea }` from `$lib/components/ui/textarea` |
| `<select>` | `import Select from "$lib/components/ui/select.svelte"` |
| `<label>` | `{ Label }` from `$lib/components/ui/label` |
| checkbox | `{ Checkbox }` from `$lib/components/ui/checkbox` |
| toggle / on-off | `{ Switch }` from `$lib/components/ui/switch` |
| pill / segmented toggles | `{ Toggle }` / `{ ToggleGroup }` |
| card layout | `{ Card, CardHeader, CardContent, ... }` |

## Button variants (common patterns)

- Primary actions: `variant="default"` or `variant="outline"`
- Sidebar nav, list rows, tabs: `variant="ghost"` + `class="h-auto w-full justify-start ..."`
- Icon-only (close, chevron): `variant="ghost" size="icon-sm"`
- Full-card / full-row click targets: `variant="ghost" class="h-auto w-full text-left ..."`
- Inline links in tables: `variant="link" class="h-auto p-0"`

## Simplified Select

Prefer `$lib/components/ui/select.svelte` wrapper:

```svelte
<Select bind:value={namespace} options={namespaceOptions()} placeholder="Select namespace" />
```

## Allowed exceptions

- Hidden `<input type="file">` or `type="hidden"` (triggered by `Button`)
- Files under `src/lib/components/ui/**` (shadcn primitives and thin wrappers)
- `<label>` wrapping `{ Checkbox }` for click-target accessibility (see `TaskFilterModal.svelte`)
- Semantic non-form elements (`<kbd>`, layout divs, terminal canvas areas)

## Do not

- Hand-copy Input/Select Tailwind classes onto raw `<input>` / `<select>`
- Build DIY toggle switches with `peer sr-only` when `Switch` exists
- Add raw modal overlays — use `Dialog`, `Sheet`, or `AlertDialog`
- Use `@/` imports — use `$lib/`

## Enforcement

ESLint rule `portal/no-raw-ui-elements` flags violations in app code. Run `pnpm lint`.
